# S2-4: Generate & Share Themed Screenshots

This sprint focuses on the "Share" part of the collaborative experience. When a log is completed, users should be able to export a beautiful image of their work to share on social media.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] `ShareModal.jsx` [NEW]
A modal UI that allows users to preview their log in different themes before downloading.
- **Themes**:
    - **Minimal**: White background, clean Sans-serif.
    - **Nocturne**: Dark background, neon/vibrant text colors.
    - **Parchment**: Aged paper texture (CSS-based), serif font (Playfair Display/serif fallback).
- **Functionality**:
    - Uses `html-to-image` to capture a hidden DOM element styled according to the selected theme.
    - Supports "Download as PNG".
    - Branding: Includes the "Collective Unconscious" logo/name at the bottom.

### [Page] [LogDetailPage.jsx](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx) [MODIFY]
- Add a "Share as Image" button that appears only when `log.status === 'COMPLETED'`.
- This button triggers the `ShareModal`.

### [Infra] Dependency Installation
- Install `html-to-image` in the `client` folder.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Test that the "Share" button only renders for completed logs.
- Test that clicking the button opens the modal.

### Manual Verification
- Complete a log.
- Open the share modal.
- Verify each theme renders correctly in the browser.
- Download the image and verify clarity, author colors, and branding.
